  "case_id": "D2N005",
  "method": "cap_only",
  "template": "sectioned",
  "summary_text": "Chief Complaint\nRight middle finger pain and tenderness.\n\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports pain and tenderness in his right middle finger following a rear-end collision four to five days ago. He describes the pain as sharp and constant, exacerbated by movement. He reports experiencing some anger during the accident. The patient also reports a hand injury and a distal phalanx fracture of the middle finger. He reports very much so pain.\n\nFindings\nExamination reveals tenderness to palpation over the distal phalanx of the right middle finger. The patient has a hand injury.\n\nAssessment\nThe patient has a distal phalanx fracture of the middle finger and a hand injury.\n\nPlan\nThe patient will receive a finger splint. The patient will receive tramadol 50 mg every 6 hours as needed for pain for two days. The patient will have a follow-up x-ray in two weeks.",
  "reference_summary": "CC:\n\nRight middle finger pain.\n\nHPI:\n\nMs. Hill is a 41-year-old female who presents today for an evaluation of right middle finger pain after she was rear-ended in a motor vehicle accident. She has no other injuries.\n\nCURRENT MEDICATIONS:\n\nDigoxin\n\nPAST MEDICAL HISTORY:\n\nAtrial Fibrillation\n\nEXAM\n\nExamination of the right middle finger shows tenderness over the distal phalanx.\n\nRESULTS\n\nX-rays of the right middle finger, 3 views obtained on today's visit shows a comminuted distal phalanx fracture.\n\nIMPRESSION\n\nRight middle finger distal phalanx fracture.\n\nPLAN\n\nAt this point, I discussed the diagnosis and treatment options with the patient. I recommend a prescription for Tramadol 50 mg every 6 hours as needed for pain, dispense 8. She is provided a finger splint and will return in 2 weeks for a follow-up x-ray. All questions were answered.",
